PROGRAM DESCRIPTION
-------------------

Program: smuth (Somatic Mutation Hierarchy)  
Usage:
 -build                  Construct the sample cell lineage trees
 -show                   Display the saved cell lineage tree(s)
 -i <arg>                Input file path (validation or vcf file)
 -o <arg>                Output file path (default: input file path)
 -n,--normal <arg>       Normal sample id (default: 0)
 -minAAFHard <arg>       Minimum AAF to robustly call an SNV for a sample (default: 0.04)
 -minAAFSoft <arg>       Minimum AAF that can allow an SNV to be called for a sample (default: 0.015)
 -gpv <arg>              P-value to detemine the minimum SNV group size (default: 0.2)
 -rpv <arg>              P-value to detemine the minimum robust SNV group size (default: 0.01)
 -e <arg>                AAF error margin (default: 0.08)
 -edit <arg>             Maximum edit distance between SNV group tags that is allowed to reassign SNVs 
 			 from one group to the other (default: 2)
 -maxClusterDist <arg>   Maximum mean AAF difference up to which two clusters can be collapsed (default: 0.2)
 -minClusterSize <arg>   Minimum size a cluster must have to be a considered a node in the network (default: 2)
 -net,--showNetwork      Display the constraint network
 -top <arg>              Number of top ranking lineage trees to display
 -tree,--showTree        Display the top ranking lineage tree
 -v,--verbose            Verbose mode
 -vcf                    Input data type is vcf (default: validation)
 -s,--save               Save the output to file
 -h,--help               Print usage
 

HOW TO RUN
----------

./smuth -build | -show -i <input_file_path> [options]

EXAMPLES
--------
#Show the top ranking tree and save the results
./smuth -build -i ../data/Patient_1.validation.txt -tree -s

#Change normal sample index
./smuth -build -i ../data/Patient_3.validation.txt -tree -n 1

#Change the SNV group size p-value (will filter out the smaller groups)
./smuth -build -i ../data/Patient_1.validation.txt -tree -gpv 0.01 

#Eliminate clusters that have fewer than 5 SNVs
./smuth -build -i ../data/Patient_3.validation.txt -n 1 -minClusterSize 5 

#Display the top 2 previously computed lineage trees
./smuth -show -i ../data/Patient_3.validation.txt -top 2

SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS
-------------------
Java Runtime Environment (JRE)


